text: Paralarinia is a genus of African orb-weaver spiders first described by M. Grasshoff in 1970. ==Species== it contains four species: *Paralarinia agnata Grasshoff, 1970 – Congo *Paralarinia bartelsi (Lessert, 1933) – South Africa *Paralarinia denisi (Lessert, 1938) – Congo *Paralarinia incerta (Tullgren, 1910) – Central, East Africa ==References== Category:Araneidae Category:Araneomorphae genera Category:Spiders of Africa
title: Paralarinia
